Since 1 month is 4 weeks, 6 months is 24 weeks.

        \begin{aligned}
            P(24) \amp= 24\cdot24^3=331776 \\
            P(3) \amp= 24\cdot3^3=648
        \end{aligned}

        So after 6 months there are 331776 flies and after 3 weeks there are 648 flies.

Based on the work about, if the car's value decreased linearly then the value of the car after t years is L(t)=20000-3000t If the value of the car depreciated exponentially, then the value of the car after t years is E(t)=20000\cdot0.85^t After 5 years,

                    \begin{aligned}
                    L(5)\amp=20000-3000(5)=5000 \\
                    E(5)\amp=20000\cdot0.85^5\approx8874
                    \end{aligned}

                After 5 years, the car will be worth \$5000 under the linear model and worth approximately \$8874 under the exponential model.
